snippet.textDisplay: Hell ya! I've been watching MCM for years and I'm excited to see you finally get an MR2! I'm from America so as far as pricing, for the turbo versions, one in great shape like that goes for $8,000-12,000. Same goes for JDM imports, but typically see them around $12,000 more often. NAs go from $1,000-4000 depending on the shape. I'm in the middle of swapping it with the JDM engine and trans right now, I got it back from the machine shop, I'm replacing all the gaskets, and just started on the timing side. Really great car, it'll be a forever car for me. Also, in the US, they stopped making them in 95. 93+ they made some major revisions to the suspension that make then sought after, but the 94-95 are more saught after. I have a 1994 NA, only 950 were made for the US, and 350 95's for the US. You see a lot of 91's because there were about 21,000 of them, they're dirt cheap to buy NA, and then you 3VZFE (V6 Camry Motor), 2GR swap them, gen 2/3/4/5 swap them with track build typically being gen 4/5, or you can balls to the wall K swap them and go for 1000 HP builds.
